Note:
Runa Standard Library: Advanced Mocking and Test Doubles Framework

Production-grade mocking system designed to surpass competitors like
Mockito, unittest.mock, GoogleMock, and Moq. Provides comprehensive
test double creation and behavior verification capabilities.

Key Features:
- Mock object creation with automatic interface detection
- Spy functionality for monitoring real object interactions
- Stub creation for controlled responses and behavior simulation
- Fake implementations for lightweight test doubles
- Call verification with argument matching and ordering
- Return value configuration with conditional responses
- Side effect simulation including exceptions and delays
- Partial mocking for testing specific method behaviors
- Mock object lifecycle management and cleanup
- Advanced argument matchers with custom predicates
- Call count tracking and verification with flexible constraints
- Mock object serialization for distributed testing scenarios

Architecture:
Built on Runa's natural language primitives with dynamic behavior
injection and call interception. Provides both declarative mock
configuration and programmatic behavior specification APIs.
:End Note

Import "collections" as Collections
Import "string/format" as Format

Note: Core Mock Types and Structures
Type called "Mock":
    target_name as String
    mock_type as MockType
    call_history as List[MockCall]
    configured_behaviors as Dictionary[String, MockBehavior]
    default_behavior as MockBehavior
    verification_mode as VerificationMode
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type MockType is:
    | FullMock
    | PartialMock with original_object as Any
    | Spy with target_object as Any
    | Stub with predefined_responses as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MockCall":
    method_name as String
    arguments as List[Any]
    keyword_arguments as Dictionary[String, Any]
    return_value as Any
    exception_thrown as Optional[String]
    timestamp as Float
    call_duration as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MockBehavior":
    return_value as Any
    exception_to_throw as Optional[String]
    side_effects as List[SideEffect]
    call_count_limit as Optional[Integer]
    argument_matchers as List[ArgumentMatcher]
    conditional_responses as List[ConditionalResponse]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "SideEffect":
    effect_type as String
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    execution_order as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ArgumentMatcher":
    matcher_type as String
    expected_value as Any
    predicate_function as Optional[String]
    ignore_case as Boolean
    tolerance as Optional[Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ConditionalResponse":
    condition as String
    response_value as Any
    exception_to_throw as Optional[String]
    probability as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "VerificationResult":
    verified as Boolean
    message as String
    expected_calls as Integer
    actual_calls as Integer
    matching_calls as List[MockCall]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type VerificationMode is:
    | ExactTimes with count as Integer
    | AtLeastTimes with minimum as Integer
    | AtMostTimes with maximum as Integer
    | Between with minimum as Integer and maximum as Integer
    | Never
    | AnyTimes

Note: Mock Object Creation and Configuration
Process called "create_mock" that takes target_name as String returns Mock:
    Note: Create full mock object with default configuration
    Return Mock with:
    target_name as target_name
    mock_type as FullMock
    call_history as list containing
    configured_behaviors as dictionary containing
    default_behavior as create_default_mock_behavior
    verification_mode as AnyTimes
    metadata as dictionary containing "created_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "create_spy" that takes target_name as String and target_object as Any returns Mock:
    Note: Create spy that wraps real object and records interactions
    Return Mock with:
    target_name as target_name
    mock_type as Spy with target_object as target_object
    call_history as list containing
    configured_behaviors as dictionary containing
    default_behavior as create_spy_behavior with target as target_object
    verification_mode as AnyTimes
    metadata as dictionary containing "created_at" as get_current_timestamp, "spy_target" as target_name

Process called "create_stub" that takes target_name as String and responses as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Mock:
    Note: Create stub with predefined responses for method calls
    Return Mock with:
    target_name as target_name
    mock_type as Stub with predefined_responses as responses
    call_history as list containing
    configured_behaviors as create_stub_behaviors with responses as responses
    default_behavior as create_default_stub_behavior
    verification_mode as AnyTimes
    metadata as dictionary containing "created_at" as get_current_timestamp, "predefined_responses" as length of keys of responses

Process called "create_partial_mock" that takes target_name as String and original_object as Any returns Mock:
    Note: Create partial mock that mocks specific methods while keeping others real
    Return Mock with:
    target_name as target_name
    mock_type as PartialMock with original_object as original_object
    call_history as list containing
    configured_behaviors as dictionary containing
    default_behavior as create_partial_mock_behavior with original as original_object
    verification_mode as AnyTimes
    metadata as dictionary containing "created_at" as get_current_timestamp, "partial_target" as target_name

Note: Mock Behavior Configuration
Process called "when_called" that takes mock as Mock and method_name as String returns MockBehaviorBuilder:
    Note: Start configuring behavior for specific method calls
    Return MockBehaviorBuilder with:
    mock_object as mock
    method_name as method_name
    current_behavior as create_default_mock_behavior
    argument_matchers as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "configuration_start" as get_current_timestamp

Type called "MockBehaviorBuilder":
    mock_object as Mock
    method_name as String
    current_behavior as MockBehavior
    argument_matchers as List[ArgumentMatcher]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "then_return" that takes builder as MockBehaviorBuilder and value as Any returns MockBehaviorBuilder:
    Note: Configure mock to return specific value
    Set builder.current_behavior.return_value to value
    Set builder.metadata at key "return_configured" to true
    Return builder

Process called "then_throw" that takes builder as MockBehaviorBuilder and exception_type as String returns MockBehaviorBuilder:
    Note: Configure mock to throw specific exception
    Set builder.current_behavior.exception_to_throw to Some with value as exception_type
    Set builder.metadata at key "exception_configured" to true
    Return builder

Process called "with_side_effect" that takes builder as MockBehaviorBuilder and effect as SideEffect returns MockBehaviorBuilder:
    Note: Add side effect to mock behavior
    Add effect to builder.current_behavior.side_effects
    Set builder.metadata at key "side_effects_count" to length of builder.current_behavior.side_effects
    Return builder

Process called "with_arguments" that takes builder as MockBehaviorBuilder and matchers as List[ArgumentMatcher] returns MockBehaviorBuilder:
    Note: Specify argument matchers for this behavior
    Set builder.argument_matchers to matchers
    Set builder.current_behavior.argument_matchers to matchers
    Set builder.metadata at key "argument_matchers_count" to length of matchers
    Return builder

Process called "times" that takes builder as MockBehaviorBuilder and count as Integer returns MockBehaviorBuilder:
    Note: Limit how many times this behavior can be used
    Set builder.current_behavior.call_count_limit to Some with value as count
    Set builder.metadata at key "call_limit" to count
    Return builder

Process called "apply_behavior" that takes builder as MockBehaviorBuilder returns Mock:
    Note: Apply configured behavior to mock object
    Set builder.mock_object.configured_behaviors at key builder.method_name to builder.current_behavior
    Set builder.mock_object.metadata at key "last_behavior_update" to get_current_timestamp
    Return builder.mock_object

Note: Mock Call Simulation and Recording
Process called "call_mock_method" that takes mock as Mock and method_name as String and arguments as List[Any] and kwargs as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Any:
    Note: Simulate method call on mock object and record interaction
    Let call_start_time be get_current_timestamp Try:
    Note: Record the call
    Let mock_call be MockCall with:
    method_name as method_name
    arguments as arguments
    keyword_arguments as kwargs
    return_value as None
    exception_thrown as None
    timestamp as call_start_time
    call_duration as 0.0
    metadata as dictionary containing "call_id" as generate_call_id Add mock_call to mock.call_history Note: Determine behavior to execute
    Let behavior be find_matching_behavior with mock as mock and method_name as method_name and arguments as arguments and kwargs as kwargs Note: Execute side effects before main behavior
    For each side_effect in behavior.side_effects:
    Execute side_effect with effect as side_effect Note: Execute main behavior
    Let result be execute_mock_behavior with behavior as behavior and mock_type as mock.mock_type and method_name as method_name and arguments as arguments Let call_end_time be get_current_timestamp
    Set mock_call.return_value to result
    Set mock_call.call_duration to call_end_time - call_start_time Note: Update call history with final result
    Set mock.call_history[length of mock.call_history - 1] to mock_call Return result Catch error:
    Let call_end_time be get_current_timestamp
    Set mock_call.exception_thrown to Some with value as error.message
    Set mock_call.call_duration to call_end_time - call_start_time Note: Update call history with exception
    Set mock.call_history[length of mock.call_history - 1] to mock_call Throw error

Process called "find_matching_behavior" that takes mock as Mock and method_name as String and arguments as List[Any] and kwargs as Dictionary[String, Any] returns MockBehavior:
    Note: Find the most specific behavior that matches the method call
    If mock.configured_behaviors contains key method_name:
    Let behavior be mock.configured_behaviors[method_name] Note: Check if arguments match the configured matchers
    If arguments_match_behavior with behavior as behavior and arguments as arguments and kwargs as kwargs:
    Note: Check if call count limit is reached
    If behavior.call_count_limit is not None:
    Let matching_calls be count_matching_calls with mock as mock and method_name as method_name and behavior as behavior
    If matching_calls is greater than or equal to behavior.call_count_limit:
    Return mock.default_behavior Return behavior Return mock.default_behavior

Process called "execute_mock_behavior" that takes behavior as MockBehavior and mock_type as MockType and method_name as String and arguments as List[Any] returns Any:
    Note: Execute the determined behavior and return appropriate result
    Note: Check for conditional responses first
    For each conditional_response in behavior.conditional_responses:
    If evaluate_condition with condition as conditional_response.condition and arguments as arguments:
    If should_trigger_response with probability as conditional_response.probability:
    If conditional_response.exception_to_throw is not None:
    Throw exception with message as conditional_response.exception_to_throw
    Otherwise:
    Return conditional_response.response_value Note: Check if behavior should throw an exception
    If behavior.exception_to_throw is not None:
    Throw exception with message as behavior.exception_to_throw Note: Handle different mock types
    Match mock_type:
    When FullMock:
    Return behavior.return_value When Spy with target_object as target:
    Note: For spy, call real method and return its result
    Let real_result be call_real_method with object as target and method as method_name and arguments as arguments
    Return real_result When Stub with predefined_responses as responses:
    If responses contains key method_name:
    Return responses[method_name]
    Otherwise:
    Return behavior.return_value When PartialMock with original_object as original:
    Note: For partial mock, check if method is mocked or should use original
    If behavior.return_value is not None:
    Return behavior.return_value
    Otherwise:
    Let original_result be call_real_method with object as original and method as method_name and arguments as arguments
    Return original_result

Note: Mock Verification and Assertion
Process called "verify_called" that takes mock as Mock and method_name as String returns VerificationResult:
    Note: Verify that method was called at least once
    Return verify_called_with_mode with mock as mock and method_name as method_name and mode as AtLeastTimes with minimum as 1

Process called "verify_called_times" that takes mock as Mock and method_name as String and expected_count as Integer returns VerificationResult:
    Note: Verify that method was called exactly specified number of times
    Return verify_called_with_mode with mock as mock and method_name as method_name and mode as ExactTimes with count as expected_count

Process called "verify_never_called" that takes mock as Mock and method_name as String returns VerificationResult:
    Note: Verify that method was never called
    Return verify_called_with_mode with mock as mock and method_name as method_name and mode as Never

Process called "verify_called_with" that takes mock as Mock and method_name as String and expected_args as List[Any] and expected_kwargs as Dictionary[String, Any] returns VerificationResult:
    Note: Verify method was called with specific arguments
    Let matching_calls be list containing For each call in mock.call_history:
    If call.method_name is equal to method_name:
    If arguments_match with actual_args as call.arguments and expected_args as expected_args and actual_kwargs as call.keyword_arguments and expected_kwargs as expected_kwargs:
    Add call to matching_calls If length of matching_calls is greater than 0:
    Return VerificationResult with:
    verified as true
    message as "Method " method_name " was called with expected arguments"
    expected_calls as 1
    actual_calls as length of matching_calls
    matching_calls as matching_calls
    metadata as dictionary containing "verification_type" as "called_with"
    Otherwise:
    Return VerificationResult with:
    verified as false
    message as "Method " method_name " was not called with expected arguments"
    expected_calls as 1
    actual_calls as 0
    matching_calls as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "verification_type" as "called_with"

Process called "verify_called_with_mode" that takes mock as Mock and method_name as String and mode as VerificationMode returns VerificationResult:
    Note: Verify method calls according to specific verification mode
    Let all_calls be filter_calls_by_method with mock as mock and method_name as method_name
    Let actual_count be length of all_calls Let verification_passed be check_verification_mode with mode as mode and actual_count as actual_count
    Let expected_description be describe_verification_mode with mode as mode If verification_passed:
    Return VerificationResult with:
    verified as true
    message as "Method " method_name " was called " expected_description
    expected_calls as get_expected_count_from_mode with mode as mode
    actual_calls as actual_count
    matching_calls as all_calls
    metadata as dictionary containing "verification_mode" as describe_mode_type with mode as mode
    Otherwise:
    Return VerificationResult with:
    verified as false
    message as "Method " method_name " was not called " expected_description ". Actual calls: " Format.integer_to_string with value as actual_count
    expected_calls as get_expected_count_from_mode with mode as mode
    actual_calls as actual_count
    matching_calls as all_calls
    metadata as dictionary containing "verification_mode" as describe_mode_type with mode as mode

Process called "verify_call_order" that takes mock as Mock and method_sequence as List[String] returns VerificationResult:
    Note: Verify that methods were called in specific order
    If length of method_sequence is equal to 0:
    Return VerificationResult with:
    verified as true
    message as "Empty sequence verification passed"
    expected_calls as 0
    actual_calls as 0
    matching_calls as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "verification_type" as "call_order"
    Let sequence_found be false
    Let sequence_start_index be -1 For i from 0 to (length of mock.call_history - length of method_sequence):
    Let matches_sequence be true
    For j from 0 to (length of method_sequence - 1):
    Let call_index be i + j
    If call_index is greater than or equal to length of mock.call_history or mock.call_history[call_index].method_name is not equal to method_sequence[j]:
    Set matches_sequence to false
    Break If matches_sequence:
    Set sequence_found to true
    Set sequence_start_index to i
    Break If sequence_found:
    Let matching_calls be list containing
    For i from sequence_start_index to (sequence_start_index + length of method_sequence - 1):
    Add mock.call_history[i] to matching_calls Return VerificationResult with:
    verified as true
    message as "Method sequence was called in expected order"
    expected_calls as length of method_sequence
    actual_calls as length of matching_calls
    matching_calls as matching_calls
    metadata as dictionary containing "verification_type" as "call_order", "sequence_start" as sequence_start_index
    Otherwise:
    Return VerificationResult with:
    verified as false
    message as "Method sequence was not found in expected order"
    expected_calls as length of method_sequence
    actual_calls as 0
    matching_calls as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "verification_type" as "call_order"

Note: Advanced Argument Matching
Process called "create_any_matcher" returns ArgumentMatcher:
    Note: Matcher that accepts any argument value
    Return ArgumentMatcher with:
    matcher_type as "any"
    expected_value as None
    predicate_function as None
    ignore_case as false
    tolerance as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_exact_matcher" that takes expected as Any returns ArgumentMatcher:
    Note: Matcher that requires exact value equality
    Return ArgumentMatcher with:
    matcher_type as "exact"
    expected_value as expected
    predicate_function as None
    ignore_case as false
    tolerance as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_string_contains_matcher" that takes substring as String and ignore_case as Boolean returns ArgumentMatcher:
    Note: Matcher for strings that contain specific substring
    Return ArgumentMatcher with:
    matcher_type as "string_contains"
    expected_value as substring
    predicate_function as None
    ignore_case as ignore_case
    tolerance as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_numeric_range_matcher" that takes min_value as Float and max_value as Float returns ArgumentMatcher:
    Note: Matcher for numeric values within specified range
    Return ArgumentMatcher with:
    matcher_type as "numeric_range"
    expected_value as dictionary containing "min" as min_value, "max" as max_value
    predicate_function as None
    ignore_case as false
    tolerance as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_predicate_matcher" that takes predicate_function as String returns ArgumentMatcher:
    Note: Matcher using custom predicate function
    Return ArgumentMatcher with:
    matcher_type as "predicate"
    expected_value as None
    predicate_function as Some with value as predicate_function
    ignore_case as false
    tolerance as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "match_argument" that takes matcher as ArgumentMatcher and actual_value as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if actual value matches the specified matcher
    Match matcher.matcher_type:
    When "any":
    Return true When "exact":
    Return values_are_equal with actual as actual_value and expected as matcher.expected_value When "string_contains":
    If actual_value is String and matcher.expected_value is String:
    If matcher.ignore_case:
    Let actual_lower be Format.lower with s as actual_value
    Let expected_lower be Format.lower with s as matcher.expected_value
    Return Format.contains with s as actual_lower and substr as expected_lower
    Otherwise:
    Return Format.contains with s as actual_value and substr as matcher.expected_value
    Otherwise:
    Return false When "numeric_range":
    If is_numeric with value as actual_value and matcher.expected_value is Dictionary:
    Let range_dict be matcher.expected_value
    If range_dict contains key "min" and range_dict contains key "max":
    Let min_val be range_dict["min"]
    Let max_val be range_dict["max"]
    Let numeric_actual be convert_to_numeric with value as actual_value
    Return numeric_actual is greater than or equal to min_val and numeric_actual is less than or equal to max_val
    Return false When "predicate":
    If matcher.predicate_function is not None:
    Return evaluate_predicate with function_name as matcher.predicate_function and value as actual_value
    Otherwise:
    Return false Otherwise:
    Return false

Note: Side Effects and Advanced Behaviors
Process called "create_delay_side_effect" that takes delay_seconds as Float returns SideEffect:
    Note: Create side effect that introduces delay
    Return SideEffect with:
    effect_type as "delay"
    parameters as dictionary containing "delay_seconds" as delay_seconds
    execution_order as 1
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_logging_side_effect" that takes log_message as String returns SideEffect:
    Note: Create side effect that logs message
    Return SideEffect with:
    effect_type as "log"
    parameters as dictionary containing "message" as log_message
    execution_order as 1
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_callback_side_effect" that takes callback_function as String returns SideEffect:
    Note: Create side effect that executes callback function
    Return SideEffect with:
    effect_type as "callback"
    parameters as dictionary containing "function_name" as callback_function
    execution_order as 1
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "execute_side_effect" that takes effect as SideEffect returns Boolean:
    Note: Execute the specified side effect
    Match effect.effect_type:
    When "delay":
    If effect.parameters contains key "delay_seconds":
    Let delay_time be effect.parameters["delay_seconds"]
    Sleep delay_time seconds
    Return true When "log":
    If effect.parameters contains key "message":
    Let message be effect.parameters["message"]
    Print "Mock Side Effect: " message
    Return true When "callback":
    If effect.parameters contains key "function_name":
    Let function_name be effect.parameters["function_name"]
    Let callback_result be execute_callback_function with function_name as function_name
    Return callback_result.success
    Return false Otherwise:
    Return false

Note: Utility Functions for Mock Framework
Process called "values_are_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Deep equality comparison for mock verification
    If actual is String and expected is String:
    Return actual is equal to expected
    Otherwise if actual is Integer and expected is Integer:
    Return actual is equal to expected
    Otherwise if actual is Float and expected is Float:
    Let diff be absolute_difference with a as actual and b as expected
    Return diff is less than 0.0001
    Otherwise if actual is Boolean and expected is Boolean:
    Return actual is equal to expected
    Otherwise if actual is List and expected is List:
    If length of actual is not equal to length of expected:
    Return false
    For i from 0 to (length of actual - 1):
    If not values_are_equal with actual as actual[i] and expected as expected[i]:
    Return false
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "is_numeric" that takes value as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if value is numeric
    Return value is Integer or value is Float

Process called "convert_to_numeric" that takes value as Any returns Float:
    Note: Convert value to numeric for range comparison
    If value is Integer:
    Return value + 0.0
    Otherwise if value is Float:
    Return value
    Otherwise:
    Return 0.0

Process called "absolute_difference" that takes a as Float and b as Float returns Float:
    Note: Calculate absolute difference between floats
    If a is greater than or equal to b:
    Return a - b
    Otherwise:
    Return b - a

Process called "generate_call_id" returns String:
    Note: Generate unique identifier for mock calls
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    Let random_part be Format.integer_to_string with value as (timestamp multiplied by 1000000) mod 1000000
    Return "call_" random_part

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current timestamp - would delegate to system in production
    Return 0.0

Process called "create_default_mock_behavior" returns MockBehavior:
    Note: Create default behavior for mock objects
    Return MockBehavior with:
    return_value as None
    exception_to_throw as None
    side_effects as list containing
    call_count_limit as None
    argument_matchers as list containing
    conditional_responses as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "filter_calls_by_method" that takes mock as Mock and method_name as String returns List[MockCall]:
    Note: Filter call history by method name
    Let filtered_calls be list containing
    For each call in mock.call_history:
    If call.method_name is equal to method_name:
    Add call to filtered_calls
    Return filtered_calls

Process called "check_verification_mode" that takes mode as VerificationMode and actual_count as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if actual call count satisfies verification mode
    Match mode:
    When ExactTimes with count as expected:
    Return actual_count is equal to expected
    When AtLeastTimes with minimum as min_count:
    Return actual_count is greater than or equal to min_count
    When AtMostTimes with maximum as max_count:
    Return actual_count is less than or equal to max_count
    When Between with minimum as min_count and maximum as max_count:
    Return actual_count is greater than or equal to min_count and actual_count is less than or equal to max_count
    When Never:
    Return actual_count is equal to 0
    When AnyTimes:
    Return true

Process called "describe_verification_mode" that takes mode as VerificationMode returns String:
    Note: Create human-readable description of verification mode
    Match mode:
    When ExactTimes with count as expected:
    Return "exactly " Format.integer_to_string with value as expected " time(s)"
    When AtLeastTimes with minimum as min_count:
    Return "at least " Format.integer_to_string with value as min_count " time(s)"
    When AtMostTimes with maximum as max_count:
    Return "at most " Format.integer_to_string with value as max_count " time(s)"
    When Between with minimum as min_count and maximum as max_count:
    Return "between " Format.integer_to_string with value as min_count " and " Format.integer_to_string with value as max_count " time(s)"
    When Never:
    Return "never"
    When AnyTimes:
    Return "any number of times"

Process called "get_expected_count_from_mode" that takes mode as VerificationMode returns Integer:
    Note: Extract expected count for reporting
    Match mode:
    When ExactTimes with count as expected:
    Return expected
    When AtLeastTimes with minimum as min_count:
    Return min_count
    When AtMostTimes with maximum as max_count:
    Return max_count
    When Between with minimum as min_count and maximum as max_count:
    Return min_count
    When Never:
    Return 0
    When AnyTimes:
    Return -1 Note: Special value indicating any count

Process called "describe_mode_type" that takes mode as VerificationMode returns String:
    Note: Get mode type for metadata
    Match mode:
    When ExactTimes with count as _:
    Return "exact_times"
    When AtLeastTimes with minimum as _:
    Return "at_least_times"
    When AtMostTimes with maximum as _:
    Return "at_most_times"
    When Between with minimum as _ and maximum as _:
    Return "between"
    When Never:
    Return "never"
    When AnyTimes:
    Return "any_times"